Plugin Development Guide for GNU Midnight Commander
===================================================

This document describes how to create plugins from scratch for mc.
It covers:

- panel plugins (filemanager virtual panels)
- editor plugins (mcedit extensions)

The authoritative declarations live in:

- lib/panel-plugin.h
- lib/editor-plugin.h

This guide reflects the current API only.  When in doubt, the header
is the source of truth.


1. Plugin Types
---------------

mc supports three plugin families:

- VFS plugins (virtual filesystems)
- Panel plugins (content providers for filemanager panels)
- Editor plugins (extensions for mcedit)

VFS plugins use mc_vfs_plugin_init() and are not the preferred starting
point for new UI-oriented features.  This guide focuses on panel and
editor plugins.


2. Common Rules
---------------

- Keep core plugin-agnostic.
  Core must not branch on a plugin's name; expose a capability flag or
  callback instead.
- Use generic callback contracts from the plugin headers.
- Return explicit status codes:
  - panel: MC_PPR_OK / MC_PPR_FAILED / MC_PPR_NOT_SUPPORTED / MC_PPR_CLOSE
  - editor: MC_EPR_OK / MC_EPR_FAILED / MC_EPR_NOT_SUPPORTED
- Avoid shell string composition when a generic host callback exists.
  Example: panel diff should use host->open_diff().
- Activation contract: if a plugin's open() / open_file_list() /
  action callback returns NULL, the previously active panel remains
  intact.  Return NULL on Cancel.


3. Panel Plugins (Filemanager)
------------------------------

In-tree references (read these before writing your own):

  src/panel-plugins/hello/       smallest working plugin
  src/panel-plugins/arcmc/       archive panels, custom columns
  src/panel-plugins/git/         shell-driven listing, custom columns
  src/panel-plugins/panelize/    list curation; LOCAL_FILES,
                                 open_file_list, menu self-registration


3.0 Lifecycle and Location

mc loads dynamic panel plugins at startup via mc_panel_plugins_load()
(invoked from filemanager.c).  The loader scans:

    $(libdir)/mc/panel-plugins/<plugin>/mc-panel-<plugin>.so

The directory is configurable at build time:

    ./configure --with-panel-plugins-dir=DIR

Each .so is dlopen'd; the loader resolves the exported symbol
"mc_panel_plugin_register" (MC_PANEL_PLUGIN_ENTRY), calls it to obtain
the descriptor, and rejects the plugin with a log warning if
api_version does not match MC_PANEL_PLUGIN_API_VERSION exactly.  No
soft/legacy fallback -- rebuild your plugin every time the header
version is bumped.

The Manage Plugins dialog (panel menu -> Manage Plugins) lets the
user enable/disable individual plugins at runtime; a disabled plugin
is unloaded and does not appear in mc_panel_plugin_list().


3.1 API Entry Point

A panel plugin module must export:

    const mc_panel_plugin_t *mc_panel_plugin_register (void);

The descriptor minimum:

- api_version = MC_PANEL_PLUGIN_API_VERSION (the header constant;
  current value is 7)
- unique name (used by mc_panel_plugin_find_by_name)
- display_name (UI label)
- proto and prefix when the plugin owns a protocol scheme
  (e.g. "git:", "docker:")
- required callbacks: open, close, get_items

The loader strictly rejects mismatched api_version; rebuild against the
header any time it changes.


3.2 Capability Flags (mc_pp_flags_t)

Set in the descriptor's .flags field.  Multiple flags may be combined.

  MC_PPF_NAVIGATE             plugin handles chdir / ".."
  MC_PPF_GET_FILES            plugin can extract files
  MC_PPF_DELETE               supports Delete (F8) via delete_items
  MC_PPF_CUSTOM_TITLE         plugin provides its own panel title text
  MC_PPF_CREATE               supports Shift-F4 (new item) via create_item
  MC_PPF_PUT_FILES            accepts files via put_file/save_file (F5/F6
                              from another panel)
  MC_PPF_SHOW_IN_MENU         add an entry to the Left/Right panel menu
  MC_PPF_SHOW_IN_DRIVE_MENU   show in the Alt-F1 / Alt-F2 drive menu
  MC_PPF_LOCAL_FILES          entries are real local paths; core uses
                              them directly for view/edit/copy/move and
                              skips the get_local_copy/unlink dance
  MC_PPF_ACCEPTS_FILE_LIST    plugin implements open_file_list(); can be
                              a destination for Find results and similar
                              list producers


3.3 Host Services (mc_panel_host_t)

What mc provides to the plugin while the panel is active:

  refresh(host)
                              redraw the panel
  set_hint(host, text)
                              show a transient hint line
  message(host, flags, title, text)
                              modal message box
  run_command(host, command, flags)
                              execute a shell command in the panel's
                              subshell
  open_diff(host, left, right)
                              two-file diff via the integrated viewer
  close_plugin(host, dir_path)
                              ask the host to tear down the plugin and
                              optionally cd to dir_path
  add_history(host, path)
                              push entry into panel directory history
  get_marked_count(host)
                              number of files the user marked
  get_next_marked(host, &cur)
                              iterate marked entries
  get_current(host)
                              currently focused entry name
  navigate_other_panel(host, dir, focus_file)
                              cd the opposite panel and optionally
                              focus a specific entry
  set_cwd(host, path)
                              set the host panel's cwd; used by plugins
                              whose listing carries absolute paths so
                              that %d/%p tokens and copy targets
                              resolve against "/" (or another base)

Fields:

  host_data                   opaque, owned by core
  focus_after                 plugin sets this string to request cursor
                              positioning after a standalone action;
                              core frees it


3.4 get_items() Contract

    mc_pp_result_t get_items (void *plugin_data, void *list);

The list parameter is a `dir_list *` cast to void*.  Cast back inside
the plugin (include src/filemanager/dir.h).

Rule: do not add the ".." entry.  Core inserts it at index 0 before
calling the plugin.

Use the shared helper mc_pp_add_entry() for plain entries; plugins
that need link_to_dir / stale_link bits should call dir_list_append
+ handle_path from src/filemanager/dir.h directly.

Minimal working example -- a panel with three fake regular files of
different sizes:

    static mc_pp_result_t
    my_get_items (void *plugin_data, void *list)
    {
        (void) plugin_data;

        mc_pp_add_entry (list, "README",  S_IFREG | 0644, 1234, time (NULL));
        mc_pp_add_entry (list, "main.c",  S_IFREG | 0644, 5678, time (NULL));
        mc_pp_add_entry (list, "build/",  S_IFDIR | 0755, 0,    time (NULL));

        return MC_PPR_OK;
    }


3.5 Optional Plugin Callbacks

Listing and content:

  chdir(plugin_data, path)             requires MC_PPF_NAVIGATE
  enter(plugin_data, fname, st)
  view(plugin_data, fname, st, plain)  return MC_PPR_OK to override F3
  get_local_copy(plugin_data, fname, &local_path)
  copy_to_local(plugin_data, fname, local_path)
                                       direct download; if NULL core
                                       falls back to get_local_copy +
                                       copy
  put_file(plugin_data, local, dest)   requires MC_PPF_PUT_FILES
  save_file(plugin_data, local, name)  requires MC_PPF_PUT_FILES
  create_item(plugin_data)             requires MC_PPF_CREATE
  delete_items(plugin_data, names[], count)  requires MC_PPF_DELETE
  handle_key(plugin_data, key)
  reload(plugin_data)                  called before get_items() during
                                       Ctrl-R (explicit refresh).  Use
                                       to re-run a command or re-stat a
                                       cached list.  NULL = cache-only
                                       refresh.
  open_file_list(host, paths, count, label)
                                       requires MC_PPF_ACCEPTS_FILE_LIST.
                                       Open a plugin panel populated
                                       with @paths (caller-owned, copy
                                       what you need).  Return NULL on
                                       cancel/empty.

UI integration:

  get_title(plugin_data)               requires MC_PPF_CUSTOM_TITLE
  get_footer(plugin_data)
  get_focus_name(plugin_data)          preferred focus item after
                                       navigation/reload
  get_help_info(plugin_data, &filename, &node)
                                       used for F1 in the plugin panel
  get_columns(plugin_data, &count)     custom column descriptors
  get_column_value(plugin_data, fname, column_id)
  get_default_format(plugin_data)      default panel format string,
                                       e.g. "half name | size | mtime";
                                       returning NULL/empty falls back
                                       to get_columns()

Sort preferences:

  default_sort_id                      mc sort id ("name", "mtime",
                                       "size", "extension", ...).
                                       Applied once at panel open.
  default_sort_reverse                 TRUE = descending


3.6 Actions and Menu Self-Registration

A plugin exposes named actions through:

    const mc_pp_action_t *actions;
    int action_count;

Each action has a label and a callback:

    void *(*callback) (mc_panel_host_t *host, const char *open_path);

Callback returns non-NULL plugin_data to activate a plugin panel, or
NULL to perform a standalone operation (e.g. open a configuration
dialog).

A plugin publishes itself into top-level menus through:

    const mc_pp_cmd_menu_entry_t *cmd_menu_entries;
    int cmd_menu_entry_count;

Each entry sets:

    label            menu text (with & accelerator); NULL = separator
    action_index     index into actions[]
    shortcut         display string for the shortcut column
    key              key code, or 0
    menu_name        MC_PP_MENU_COMMAND or MC_PP_MENU_PANEL.  NULL
                     defaults to MC_PP_MENU_COMMAND.

Core scans the registry per menu and appends entries via
panel_plugin_collect_menu_entries(); the menu builders carry no
plugin-specific strings.


3.7 Shared Helpers

  mc_pp_add_entry(list, name, mode, size, mtime)
                              append one entry to a dir_list
  mc_pp_rename_with_ext(&local_path, fname)
                              rename a temp file to preserve fname's
                              extension (for viewers/syntax)
  mc_pp_join_path(base, name) / mc_pp_path_up(path)
                              UNIX-path helpers; no double slashes


3.8 Registry

  mc_panel_plugin_list()                   GSList of all registered
                                           plugins, in registration
                                           order
  mc_panel_plugin_find_by_name(name)       lookup by descriptor name
  mc_panel_plugin_find_by_prefix(prefix)   lookup by URL prefix

Producers (such as Find) ask the core layer rather than the registry
directly:

  panel_plugin_have_file_list_sink()       any sink loaded?
  panel_plugin_open_file_list(panel, paths, count, label)
                                           0 sinks -> FALSE; 1 sink ->
                                           activate; >=2 -> show
                                           "Send to panel" picker.


3.9 Build Integration

Plugin Makefile.am skeleton (src/panel-plugins/myplugin/Makefile.am):

    myplugindir = $(panel_plugins_dir)/myplugin
    myplugin_LTLIBRARIES = mc-panel-myplugin.la

    mc_panel_myplugin_la_SOURCES = myplugin.c
    mc_panel_myplugin_la_CPPFLAGS = $(GLIB_CFLAGS) -I$(top_srcdir)
    mc_panel_myplugin_la_LDFLAGS = -module -avoid-version
    mc_panel_myplugin_la_LIBADD = $(GLIB_LIBS)

The mandatory `-module -avoid-version` libtool flags produce
`mc-panel-myplugin.so` rather than a versioned shared library, which
is what the loader expects.

Wire-up:

- src/panel-plugins/Makefile.am: add `myplugin` to both `SUBDIRS` and
  `DIST_SUBDIRS`.
- configure.ac: append the file to `AC_CONFIG_FILES`:

      src/panel-plugins/myplugin/Makefile

Build / install cycle for iterating on a plugin:

    autoreconf -fi              # only after Makefile.am / configure.ac edits
    cd <build-dir>
    ../mc/configure --prefix=/usr ...   # if not configured yet
    make
    sudo make install
    # restart mc; check that the plugin appears in Manage Plugins.

The loader writes rejection reasons (version mismatch, missing
required callbacks) directly to stderr; redirect mc's stderr or check
the terminal scrollback if the plugin silently fails to load.


3.10 Minimal Skeleton

A buildable plugin that loads, registers in the drive menu, and shows
three fake files when activated:

    #include <config.h>

    #include <sys/stat.h>
    #include <time.h>

    #include "lib/global.h"
    #include "lib/panel-plugin.h"

    static void *
    my_open (mc_panel_host_t *host, const char *open_path)
    {
        (void) host;
        (void) open_path;
        return g_new0 (int, 1);   /* opaque plugin_data */
    }

    static void
    my_close (void *plugin_data)
    {
        g_free (plugin_data);
    }

    static mc_pp_result_t
    my_get_items (void *plugin_data, void *list)
    {
        (void) plugin_data;
        mc_pp_add_entry (list, "README", S_IFREG | 0644, 1234, time (NULL));
        mc_pp_add_entry (list, "main.c", S_IFREG | 0644, 5678, time (NULL));
        mc_pp_add_entry (list, "build/", S_IFDIR | 0755, 0,    time (NULL));
        return MC_PPR_OK;
    }

    static const mc_panel_plugin_t my_plugin = {
        .api_version  = MC_PANEL_PLUGIN_API_VERSION,
        .name         = "myplugin",
        .display_name = N_ ("My Plugin"),
        .proto        = "my",
        .prefix       = "my:",
        .flags        = MC_PPF_SHOW_IN_DRIVE_MENU,

        .open         = my_open,
        .close        = my_close,
        .get_items    = my_get_items,
    };

    const mc_panel_plugin_t *
    mc_panel_plugin_register (void)
    {
        return &my_plugin;
    }

After `sudo make install` and restarting mc, the plugin shows up in
the Alt-F1 / Alt-F2 drive menu under "My Plugin"; pressing Enter on
it opens a panel populated by my_get_items().


3.11 Activation Entry Points

How a user invokes a panel plugin depends on which capability flags
are set and what self-registration entries the descriptor declares:

  Drive menu (Alt-F1 / Alt-F2)
                              MC_PPF_SHOW_IN_DRIVE_MENU.  The
                              display_name appears as a menu entry;
                              activation calls open(host, cwd).

  Left / Right panel menu
                              MC_PPF_SHOW_IN_MENU, plus an entry in
                              cmd_menu_entries with
                              menu_name = MC_PP_MENU_PANEL.  Activates
                              the chosen action.

  Command menu
                              cmd_menu_entries entry with
                              menu_name = MC_PP_MENU_COMMAND.  Used
                              for actions reachable via Alt-letter or
                              a keymap binding.

  URL prefix
                              When the panel descriptor sets `prefix`
                              (e.g. "my:"), the host treats it as a
                              protocol for plugin activation.  Other
                              plugins / core code can call
                              panel_plugin_activate_by_path("my:foo").

  Programmatic file-list
                              MC_PPF_ACCEPTS_FILE_LIST with
                              open_file_list().  Producers such as
                              Find pick the plugin via
                              panel_plugin_open_file_list() -- no
                              direct user choice unless multiple
                              sinks exist.

A plugin can advertise multiple paths simultaneously (drive menu +
self-registered Command menu + file-list sink); the registry handles
each independently.


4. Editor Plugins (mcedit)
--------------------------

In-tree references:

  src/editor-plugins/spell/      classic plugin: open + activate +
                                 configure with no dynamic actions
  src/editor-plugins/ctags/      self-registered menu entries, named
                                 actions, dynamic shortcut resolver


4.0 Lifecycle and Location

Editor plugins are loaded at editor startup.  The loader scans:

    $(libdir)/mc/editor-plugins/<plugin>/mc-editor-<plugin>.so

The directory is configurable at build time:

    ./configure --with-editor-plugins-dir=DIR

Each .so is dlopen'd; the loader resolves
"mc_editor_plugin_register" (MC_EDITOR_PLUGIN_ENTRY) and rejects the
plugin if api_version != MC_EDITOR_PLUGIN_API_VERSION.  Rejection
reasons go to stderr.

A second integration mode (builtin) registers descriptors from core
startup and links the plugin sources directly into the editor binary;
see src/editor-plugins/builtin-plugins.c.  Use it only for transition
or bootstrapping -- prefer dynamic mode for new plugins.


4.1 API Entry Point

An editor plugin module must export:

    const mc_editor_plugin_t *mc_editor_plugin_register (void);

The descriptor minimum:

- api_version = MC_EDITOR_PLUGIN_API_VERSION (current value is 4)
- unique name
- display_name
- required callbacks: open, close

Strict version check at load.


4.2 Capability Flags (mc_ep_flags_t)

  MC_EPF_HAS_MENU            plugin contributes entries to a top-level
                             editor menu (actions[] + cmd_menu_entries[])


4.3 Host Services (mc_editor_host_t)

  redraw(host)
                             redraw the editor window
  message(host, flags, title, text)
                             modal message box
  get_cursor_word(host, edit)
                             word under cursor; NULL if not on a word.
                             Caller frees with g_free()
  get_current_file(host, edit)
                             absolute path of the open file or NULL;
                             caller frees
  get_cursor_line(host, edit)
                             1-based line number; 0 if unavailable
  jump_to(host, edit, file, line)
                             open file at line; pushes the current
                             position onto the navigation stack
  insert_text(host, edit, text, remove_before)
                             insert at cursor after deleting
                             remove_before bytes backwards

Fields:

  host_data                  opaque, owned by core


4.4 Plugin Callbacks

  activate(plugin_data, edit)
                             primary action invoked from the Plugins
                             menu / shortcut
  configure(plugin_data, edit)
                             open settings dialog
  handle_action(plugin_data, command, edit)
                             dispatch a menu-command id
  query_state(plugin_data, edit, &state)
                             fill mc_ep_state_t (available / enabled /
                             reason) for menu and shortcut logic
  handle_key(plugin_data, key, edit)
                             raw key interception
  handle_event(plugin_data, edit, event_id, payload)
                             generic event channel; see MC_EP_EVENT_*
  on_file_open(plugin_data, edit)
                             callback fired when a file is opened
  on_file_close(plugin_data, edit)
                             callback fired when a file is closed

State contract (mc_ep_state_t):

  available                  plugin can operate in the current
                             environment (binaries present, etc.)
  enabled                    action is currently usable
  reason                     optional explanation shown to the user


4.5 Actions, Menu Entries, Events

A plugin exposes actions through:

    const mc_ep_action_t *actions;
    int action_count;

Each entry has a label and a direct callback:

    mc_ep_result_t (*callback) (void *plugin_data, void *edit);

The callback is invoked directly when the user picks the menu item or
fires the action keymap binding; activate / handle_action are not used
for it.

Top-level menu integration:

    const mc_ep_cmd_menu_entry_t *cmd_menu_entries;
    int cmd_menu_entry_count;

Each entry sets:

    menu_name        MC_EP_MENU_COMMAND or MC_EP_MENU_NAVIGATE
    label            menu text (with & accelerator); NULL = separator
    action_index     index into actions[]
    shortcut         display string for the shortcut column; NULL =
                     omit.  Overridden at menu-build time if the plugin
                     defines get_menu_shortcut().

Optional dynamic shortcut resolver:

    char *(*get_menu_shortcut) (int action_index);

Returns a newly-allocated string (caller frees with g_free) or NULL to
fall back to the static shortcut text.

Events delivered via handle_event(plugin_data, edit, event_id, payload):

  MC_EP_EVENT_FILE_SAVED      file written; payload = const char *path
  MC_EP_EVENT_FILE_RENAMED    Save As completed; payload = new path
  MC_EP_EVENT_FOCUS_IN        editor window got focus
  MC_EP_EVENT_FOCUS_OUT       editor window lost focus


4.6 Registry

  mc_editor_plugin_list()
  mc_editor_plugin_find_by_name(name)


